{"TopicId":91282,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"For Questions That Don\u0026#039;t Merit Their Own Thread","CreatedByName":"Skyler4856","CreatedById":76452,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-26T04:12:34Z","PageNum":311,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-29T09:42:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it can, the space pirates can grapple and board!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-07-29T09:42:22Z\u0022 title=\u002207/29/2022 09:42  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 29, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tomf","CreatedById":57809,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-29T10:56:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you look at the pork chop plot you can pick your departure date on the horizontal axis, and the arrival date on the vertical and it will tell you how much Delta v you need, so if you have the Delta v and you pick an arrival date before the first crafts arrival date the later craft will overtake\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LHACK4142","CreatedById":208897,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-31T02:00:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any word for when a person tells you to do something in a nasty way, and you want to disobey just because the person said it so nastily?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-31T04:21:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221920x\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022150.15\u0022 height=\u0022500\u0022 width=\u0022333\u0022 src=\u0022https://avatars.mds.yandex.net/get-kinopoisk-image/1599028/0502585a-2ab5-4aef-a359-eb3c95af1b83/1920x\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-31T16:37:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224158957\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659087730\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/29/2022 at 11:42 AM, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it can, the space pirates can grapple and board!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcept if the other ship does an burn to change its trajectory. Or do an burn in your direction then you are 100 meters away.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nNo the Kzin lesson is not true outside of stuff like this or as an close in weapon against missiles with an very powerful engine but even\u00A0 with multi megaton pulse nuclear or similar powerful NSVR or fusion engine you would be in range of conversational artillery long before the engine was an significant danger to the attacker, you would better try to dodge the shells than have them hit your engine.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224159681\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659232826\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208897\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LHACK4142\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, LHACK4142 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any word for when a person tells you to do something in a nasty way, and you want to disobey just because the person said it so nastily?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf its an superior, probably if you complain to higher up and it was not urgent. If your shift leader call you out nastily and told to bring him an\u00A0fire extinguishing and call the fire department you do as told and complain later. If it was doing unplanned overtime because of low on staff but no serious urgency, again complain up and have an excuse.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-31T17:58:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBelligerence, insolence and indolence come to mind.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry - guess I\u0027ve been a boss too long.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-07-31T17:58:14Z\u0022 title=\u002207/31/2022 05:58  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 31, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by JoeSchmuckatelli\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-31T20:10:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a radius relationship between planets or moons in a 3:2 resonance around the primary?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(I.e. If I want to put a pair of moons in a stable 3:2 resonance in Universe Sandbox, can i place the first one and then use some multiple of the distance from the planet to use as the radial distance for the second moon?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr is it a whole lot more complicated than that?}\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-31T20:13:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nT = 2*pi *r\u003Csup\u003E3/2\u003C/sup\u003E\u00A0/ sqrt(GM)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nM = mass of the central body\u003Cbr\u003E\nr = orbit radius (semiaxis)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nT - revolution period\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nT ~ r\u003Csup\u003E3/2\u003C/sup\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-31T23:11:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224159844\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659298431\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nT = 2*pi *r\u003Csup\u003E3/2\u003C/sup\u003E\u00A0/ sqrt(GM)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nM = mass of the central body\u003Cbr\u003E\nr = orbit radius (semiaxis)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nT - revolution period\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nT ~ r\u003Csup\u003E3/2\u003C/sup\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHate to ask: can you break this down a bit more Barney style?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI need more words to know what I\u0027m looking at, pazhalsta\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SOXBLOX","CreatedById":204106,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-01T02:09:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154477-joeschmuckatelli/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022154477\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154477-joeschmuckatelli/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JoeSchmuckatelli\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0These were some of my favorite videos! Like an Irish version of Bob Ross, with \u0022happy little planets\u0022 instead of \u0022happy little trees\u0022.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/videoseries?list=PLduA6tsl3gyjeLV81Fwcxv2mHqQ_chuIO\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a lot more on his channel worth watching; both the new and old stuff is good. Enjoy!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe second vid should have more resonance stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-01T02:48:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224159901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659319750\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204106\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SOXBLOX\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, SOXBLOX said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154477-joeschmuckatelli/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022154477\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154477-joeschmuckatelli/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JoeSchmuckatelli\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0These were some of my favorite videos! Like an Irish version of Bob Ross, with \u0022happy little planets\u0022 instead of \u0022happy little trees\u0022.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/videoseries?list=PLduA6tsl3gyjeLV81Fwcxv2mHqQ_chuIO\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a lot more on his channel worth watching; both the new and old stuff is good. Enjoy!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe second vid should have more resonance stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDude!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTotally awesome, and on point.\u00A0 Esp. the part about \u0027two major moons never come withing 10 planetary radii of each other\u0027.\u00A0 (Never heard of that; but it\u0027s something I\u0027ve wondered about).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLove lines like, \u0027Intense bout of number vomit\u0027!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, question time:\u00A0 Why does the planetary Hill Sphere have \u0027a\u0027 as a parameter?\u00A0 (Semi-major axis of the planet in AU)?\u00A0 Is this because the star\u0027s mass diminishes the efficacy of the planet\u0027s mass to hold onto a moon the closer it is to the star?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-01T03:52:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224159880\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659309079\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbreak this down\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nResonance n:k is an orbital periods ratio.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe orbital period is proportional to the orbit semiaxis \u003Csup\u003E1.5\u003C/sup\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nT ~ r\u003Csup\u003E3/2\u003C/sup\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, if T\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003ET\u003Csub\u003E1\u003C/sub\u003E = n:k, then r\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003Er\u003Csub\u003E1\u003C/sub\u003E = (n:k)\u003Csup\u003E2/3\u003C/sup\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nResonance T\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003ET\u003Csub\u003E1\u003C/sub\u003E = 3:2 \u2192\u00A0r\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003Er\u003Csub\u003E1\u003C/sub\u003E = (3:2)\u003Csup\u003E2/3\u003C/sup\u003E\u00A0~= 1.31.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224159911\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659322112\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n57 minutes ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy does the planetary Hill Sphere have \u0027a\u0027 as a parameter?\u00A0 (Semi-major axis of the planet \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Eorbit\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E in AU)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause the Hill Sphere, the Sphere of Influence, etc. are describing which one of two heavy bodies on the bed is pulling the blanket more strongly at that distance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, the farther is the heavier body (the star), the more room is owned by the lesser body (the planet) to keep its moons there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-01T04:12:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224159925\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659325932\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause the Hill Sphere, the Sphere of Influence, etc. are describing which one of two heavy bodies on the bed is pulling the blanket more strongly at that distance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, the farther is the heavier body (the star), the more room is owned by the lesser body (the planet) to keep its moons there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGot it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224159925\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659325932\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nResonance n:k is an orbital periods ratio.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe orbital period is proportional to the orbit semiaxis \u003Csup\u003E1.5\u003C/sup\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nT ~ r\u003Csup\u003E3/2\u003C/sup\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, if T\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003ET\u003Csub\u003E1\u003C/sub\u003E = n:k, then r\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003Er\u003Csub\u003E1\u003C/sub\u003E = (n:k)\u003Csup\u003E2/3\u003C/sup\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nResonance T\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003ET\u003Csub\u003E1\u003C/sub\u003E = 3:2 \u2192\u00A0r\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003Er\u003Csub\u003E1\u003C/sub\u003E = (3:2)\u003Csup\u003E2/3\u003C/sup\u003E\u00A0~= 1.31.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t got it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... but thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-01T17:56:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhy are backlit keyboards so useless. except for perhaps night use, keyboards with fully addressable leds are being grossly underutilized.\u00A0it seems there is a lot you can do with application context. like color coding keys to onscreen functions and illuminating shortcuts when the appropriate modifiers are pressed. seems like its a grossly underutilized capability.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-01T19:26:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224160072\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659376573\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nuke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Nuke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhy are backlit keyboards so useless. except for perhaps night use, keyboards with fully addressable leds are being grossly underutilized.\u00A0it seems there is a lot you can do with application context. like color coding keys to onscreen functions and illuminating shortcuts when the appropriate modifiers are pressed. seems like its a grossly underutilized capability.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a very fancy laptop that has that capability... and I just can\u0027t be bothered to use that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-01T20:03:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224160072\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659376573\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nuke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Nuke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhy are backlit keyboards so useless. except for perhaps night use, keyboards with fully addressable leds are being grossly underutilized.\u00A0it seems there is a lot you can do with application context. like color coding keys to onscreen functions and illuminating shortcuts when the appropriate modifiers are pressed. seems like its a grossly underutilized capability.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause the people most likely to use that functionality have the least money to spend on keyboards.\u00A0 Matter of scale, too, most likely.\u00A0 Selling 500 keyboards with cool features world wide is a lot less profitable than selling a basic keyboard in lots of 500 to 100 different countries.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-01T20:52:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nits almost always a vanity feature with no way to use for practical applications.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-02T18:22:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224160123\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659387159\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nuke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, Nuke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nits almost always a vanity feature with no way to use for practical applications.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan see plenty of use for it but it need to be standardized, had been nice if keys changed depe